---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
const title = "The Art of Performance Tour - Alexis Morin";
---

<Base title={title}>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/aop.css" />
  </Fragment>

  <div class="body-img bdimg-aop">
    <video
      class="share-video"
      id="hero-share-video"
      poster="https://thumbs.gfycat.com/SingleLateAmazondolphin-poster.jpg"
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
    >
      <source
        id="webmSource"
        src="/images/projects/aop/SingleLateAmazondolphin.webm"
        type="video/webm"
      />
      <source
        id="mp4Source"
        src="/images/projects/aop/SingleLateAmazondolphin.mp4"
        type="video/mp4"
      />
    </video>
  </div>

  <div id="intro">
    <h3 class="tagline mobile-glass" style="color: white;">
      Jaguar Art of Performance Tour
    </h3>
  </div>

  <div class="content" id="aopintro">
    <section>
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="col-12">
          <h2>Jaguar Art of Performace Tour (捷豹 感知性能美学)</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12">
          <p>
            A collaboration with Jaguar Land Rover and Imagination; The Art of
            Performance Tour brings forward Jaguar Land Rover's classic British
            Heritage in an exposé that bridges trusted performace to the way
            humans connect with Jaguar's powerful machines.
          </p>
          <p>
            Art of Performance marries the iconic design language of Jaguar
            vehicles with 3 digital installations in 20 cities across China.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content contribution">
    <section>
      <div class="col-xs-12 center">
        <p>My contribution to the projects were:</p>
        <h3>For all activations:</h3>
        <ul style="list-style-type: circle; margin-left: 20px">
          <li>imagine concepts for digital activations,</li>
          <li>validate concepts for brand and local culture fit,</li>
          <li>ensure quality, stability, and deployability of activations.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>For the World Record Cam:</h3>
        <ul style="list-style-type: circle; margin-left: 20px">
          <li>hardware design for photo booth installation,</li>
          <li>design the content delivery pipeline,</li>
          <li>
            end-to-end implementation of the required Android &amp; Mac apps,
          </li>
          <li>video and audio editing of shareable souvenir,</li>
          <li>UX &amp; UI Design on remote control tablet,</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>For the Reactive Wall:</h3>
        <ul style="list-style-type: circle; margin-left: 20px">
          <li>
            prototype visuals and concepts to capture an accurate feel for the
            participants,
          </li>
          <li>
            produce design and experience specifications for distribution to
            remote development teams,
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>For the Paint Studio:</h3>
        <ul style="list-style-type: circle; margin-left: 20px">
          <li>
            source local artists to create blank-canvas sketches of Jaguar cars,
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <span class="am-bold">Client:</span> Jaguar Land Rover&trade; <br />
          <span class="am-bold">Team:</span> Mauricio Estrella, Sam McMorran, Samuel
          Walsh, Iain Greenhalgh <br />
          <span class="am-bold">Agency:</span> The Imagination Group <br />
          <span class="am-bold">Role:</span> Senior Creative <br />
          <span class="am-bold">Status:</span> Deployed to 20 cities across China
          from January to March 2016 <br />
          <span class="am-bold">Timeline:</span> December 2015
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-md-12 center">
        <div class="col-sm-4">
          <h3>1. World Record Cam</h3>
          <img src="/images/projects/aop/photo-booth.jpg" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
          <h3>2. Reactive Wall</h3>
          <img src="/images/projects/aop/particle-wall.jpg" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
          <h3>3. Paint Studio</h3>
          <img src="/images/projects/aop/paint-a-jaguar.jpg" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="col-12">
          <h2>World Record Cam</h2>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <p>
              I led the design for hardware, software, and implementation of the
              World Record Cam. In this activation, participants would dress up
              as legendary stunt driver Terry Grant, place themselves in a photo
              booth, receive a countdown and a prompt, after which an automated
              remote-controlled rig would snap a F-PACE themed high-speed
              motion-photo to be shared on WeChat (Chinese social media).
            </p>
            <p>
              This activation strategically re-used code, and hardware design
              from a previous installation for Ford Motors which occured at the
              New Delhi Auto Show 2016.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <figure>
              <img
                src="/images/projects/aop/photo_booth_1.jpg"
                title="Jaguar-themed backdrop for taking the motion-photo"
                alt="Jaguar-themed backdrop for taking the motion-photo"
                width="100%"
              />
              <figcaption>
                Jaguar-themed backdrop for taking the motion-photo
              </figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <figure>
              <video
                class="share-video"
                preload="none"
                poster="/images/projects/aop/slo-mo-capture.jpg"
                controls
                muted
                height="331"
                onclick="this.paused?this.play():this.pause();"
              >
                <source
                  id="webmSource"
                  src="/images/projects/aop/slo-mo-capture.webm"
                  type="video/webm"
                />
                <source
                  id="mp4Source"
                  src="/images/projects/aop/slo-mo-capture.mp4"
                  type="video/mp4"
                />
                <img
                  title="Sorry, your browser doesn't support HTML5 video."
                  src="/images/projects/aop/slo-mo-capture.jpg"
                />
              </video>
              <figcaption>Slo-mo souvenir, shareable on WeChat</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <figure>
              <div
                style="
                  width: 100%;
                  height: 0;
                  padding-bottom: 56%;
                  position: relative;
                "
              >
                <iframe
                  src="https://giphy.com/embed/SXfKkYjOlC9tUCmXIL"
                  width="100%"
                  height="100%"
                  style="position: absolute"
                  frameborder="0"
                  class="giphy-embed"
                  allowfullscreen></iframe>
              </div>
              <figcaption>
                Early prototype of a tablet-controlled camera rig.
              </figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="col-12">
          <h2>Reactive Wall</h2>
          <p>
            The Jaguar F-PACE is a technologically advanced vehicle, passively
            attentive to its driver's every movement. To embody this concept, we
            invisioned a large interactive wall which evolves and reacts as
            passerbys come and go.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
          <figure>
            <img
              src="/images/projects/aop/reactive_wall_1.jpg"
              title="Reactive Wall Setup for Suzhou, Jiangsu province"
              alt="Reactive Wall Setup for Suzhou, Jiangsu province"
              width="100%"
            />
            <figcaption>
              Reactive Wall Setup for Suzhou, Jiangsu province
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <figure>
          <iframe
            width="100%"
            height="506"
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_INVFX7-pB0"
            frameborder="0"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
            allowfullscreen></iframe>
          <figcaption>
            Video compilation of the effects available on the reactive wall.
            <br />
            Large spots of particles indicate a person passing by.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <figure>
          <iframe
            width="100%"
            height="506"
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/R4mehM33hzU"
            frameborder="0"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
            allowfullscreen></iframe>
          <figcaption>
            Progress video of the Reactive Wall still in development, <br />
            with some explanations from the Producer on the project.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="col-12">
          <h2>Paint Studio</h2>
          <p>
            Just as the car designers at Jaguar bring vehicles to life through
            sketching, so can participants with the Jaguar Paint Studio.
          </p>
          <p>
            Provided with 6 artist-drawn sketches of cars, and 4 color
            pallettes, participants could bring their a car sketch to life on a
            digital screen, using a real paintbrush.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <figure>
            <img
              src="/images/projects/aop/paint_studio_1.jpg"
              title="A younger participant, choosing a color palette."
              alt="A younger participant, choosing a color palette."
              width="100%"
            />
            <figcaption>
              A younger participant, choosing a color palette.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <figure>
            <video
              class="share-video"
              preload="none"
              poster="/images/projects/aop/paint-wall-video-poster.jpg"
              controls
              muted
              onclick="this.paused?this.play():this.pause();"
              width="100%"
            >
              <source
                id="webmSource"
                src="/images/projects/aop/paint-wall-video.webm"
                type="video/webm"
              />
              <source
                id="mp4Source"
                src="/images/projects/aop/paint-wall-video.mp4"
                type="video/mp4"
              />
              <img
                title="Sorry, your browser doesn't support HTML5 video."
                src="/images/projects/aop/paint-wall-video-poster.jpg"
              />
            </video>
            <figcaption>
              A participant adding the final touches to her piece.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script>
    var isMobile = /iPhone|iPad|iPod|Android/i.test(navigator.userAgent);
    (function () {
      resizeIntroDiv();
      if (!isMobile) {
        window.onresize = function () {
          resizeIntroDiv();
        };
      } else {
        sizeBg();
      }
    })();
  </script>
</Base>
